      "title": "Set up",
      "content": "Let $U$ = undergraduates, $G$ = graduates, $P$ = postdoctoral students. The problem gives $U = 0.715P$, $G = 0.45U$, and $G = 6{,}435$. The goal is $U + P$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve",
      "content": "From $G = 0.45U$: $U = \\dfrac{6{,}435}{0.45} = 14{,}300$. From $U = 0.715P$: $P = \\dfrac{14{,}300}{0.715} = 20{,}000$. Sum: $14{,}300 + 20{,}000 = 34{,}300$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Answer",
      "content": "<strong>34300</strong> is correct."
    }
